  "text": "Kubernetes watch event delivery path traces the journey of data changes from the etcd storage backend to client applications. The chain consists of six key components across three repositories:\n\n1. **etcd MVCC Store (watchableStore)** - In etcd-io/etcd at server/mvcc/watchable_store.go: The watchableStore struct manages watchers and generates events when keys are modified in the MVCC (Multi-Version Concurrency Control) key-value store. It maintains synced and unsynced watcher groups and forwards events through channels to registered watchers.\n\n2. **etcd Watch Stream (watchStream)** - In etcd-io/etcd at server/mvcc/watcher.go: The watchStream struct aggregates watch events from the MVCC store. It manages multiple individual watchers sharing one streaming channel and collects events from the underlying watchable interface, making them available through a single Chan() interface that forwards WatchResponse objects.\n\n3. **etcd Server Watch Stream (serverWatchStream)** - In etcd-io/etcd at server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/watch.go: The serverWatchStream struct implements the gRPC server-side stream that receives watch events from the MVCC watchStream and sends them to connected gRPC clients. It runs sendLoop() and recvLoop() goroutines that handle event forwarding and receive watch creation/cancellation requests from clients.\n\n4. **Kubernetes API Server Cacher (Cacher)** - In kubernetes/kubernetes at staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher/cacher.go: The Cacher struct serves as the watch entry point for the API server. It receives watch events from etcd and maintains internal cache state. Its Watch() method creates watch interfaces that clients connect to, and it dispatches events to multiple watchers through the watchCache.\n\n5. **Kubernetes Watch Cache (watchCache)** - In kubernetes/kubernetes at staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher/watch_cache.go: The watchCache struct maintains a sliding window of recent object changes (up to 75 seconds of history by default). It implements event buffering and filtering, dispatching watchCacheEvent objects to registered watchers through their registered eventHandler callbacks.\n\n6. **Client-side Reflector (Reflector)** - In kubernetes/client-go at tools/cache/reflector.go: The Reflector struct watches a specified resource on the client side and synchronizes all changes to a local store. It receives watch events through the watch.Interface ResultChan() channel from the API server and processes them by adding, updating, or deleting items in its local cache store.\n\nThe event flow: etcd MVCC changes → watchableStore → watchStream → serverWatchStream (gRPC) → Kubernetes API server → Cacher → watchCache → Reflector → client-side store. Each hop adds processing, filtering, or buffering to ensure reliable, efficient event delivery from the persistent storage backend to client applications."
}

